{"id":320847,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tajima_Province","text":"was an old province of Japan in the area of Hy\u014Dgo Prefecture on the island of Honsh\u016B. It was sometimes called.\nThe province had borders with Harima, Inaba, Tamba, and Tango provinces.\nThe ancient provincial capital city was near Hidaka.\nHistory.\nIn the Meiji period, the provinces of Japan were converted into prefectures. The maps of Japan and Tajima Province were reformed in the 1870s.\nShrines and Temples.\n\"Izushi jinja\" was the chief Shinto shrine (\"ichinomiya\") of Tajima.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"List_of_Provinces_of_Japan","surface_form":"old province","offset":7},{"uri":"Japan","surface_form":"Japan","offset":23},{"uri":"Hy%C5%8Dgo_Prefecture","surface_form":"Hy\u014Dgo Prefecture","offset":44},{"uri":"Honsh%C5%AB","surface_form":"Honsh\u016B","offset":78},{"uri":"Border","surface_form":"border","offset":128},{"uri":"Harima_Province","surface_form":"Harima","offset":141},{"uri":"Inaba_Province","surface_form":"Inaba","offset":149},{"uri":"Tamba_Province","surface_form":"Tamba","offset":156},{"uri":"Tango_Province","surface_form":"Tango","offset":167},{"uri":"Capital_(city)","surface_form":"capital city","offset":207},{"uri":"Hidaka%2C_Hy%C5%8Dgo","surface_form":"Hidaka","offset":229},{"uri":"Meiji_period","surface_form":"Meiji period","offset":253},{"uri":"Reform","surface_form":"reform","offset":366},{"uri":"Izushi_jinja","surface_form":"Izushi jinja","offset":411},{"uri":"Shinto_shrine","surface_form":"Shinto shrine","offset":439},{"uri":"Ichinomiya","surface_form":"ichinomiya","offset":455}]}